                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note mentions Wäldä Dawit, who’s baptismal name is Wäldä Kidos, as the donor.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#126v">Fol. 126v</locus>: Record concerning a dispute (?).<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written in a crude hand in a pencil and mentions names fitawrari Lämläm, qes Gäbrä Ṣadǝq and qes Gäbrä ʾAb.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Tämälläs-sign indicating the place where the omission, written in the upper margin, belongs: fol. 14vb.&#xD;
- The scribe used compressed script on fols. 29rb-va, 47ra-rb, 51va—52ra, 53rb-vb, 59vb, 61va-vb, 125ra-126va.&#xD;
- Corrections written interlineally: e.g., fols. 26ra, 35vb, 43ra.&#xD;
- Chains of black and red dots as text dividers: e.g., fols. 26rb, 124vb, 126vb.&#xD;
- Pen trial on fol. 127r.</item>
                     </list>
